Dizzyle wrote a review Oct 2018
Ho Chi Minh3 contributions1 helpful vote
Good location but unprofessional staff and services
The hotel is just right in front of the beach so its its highest advantage. In general, its overpriced. The infinity pool is under maintenance without any prior notice to guests. Check-in and check-out process took too long without any reasons. Staff kept receiving request but no futher actions taken. Room is deisgned as an apartment with various types of kitchen equipment, then most of them could function normally. For example, the auto coffee machine is provided without the coffee capsules.
Responded Oct 19, 2018
